      <h3>Pricing Analysis</h3>
      <p>At $32/month (annual), the Hobby plan offers solid value for small businesses testing AI customer support: 500 message credits, access to all AI models, 5 AI Actions, and basic analytics. However, 500 credits can disappear quickly if using premium models — at 5 credits per response with Claude Opus, that is only 100 conversations per month. The Standard plan at $120/month is the most popular tier, offering 4,000 credits (800-4,000 conversations depending on model choice), 8 AI Actions, helpdesk integration, voice support, and API access. The jump from Hobby to Standard is 275%, which is significant for growing businesses. Pro at $400/month targets higher-volume operations with 15,000 credits and advanced analytics.</p>
      <p>Compared to competitors: Tidio's Lyro AI starts at free (50 conversations/month) and scales to ~$50/month for 1,000 conversations. Intercom Fin charges approximately $29/seat/month plus $0.99 per resolution. CustomGPT AI starts at $89/month. Chatbase's model flexibility comes at a premium over simpler alternatives, but the ability to choose from 15+ models gives it a flexibility advantage that no competitor matches at this price point.</p>

      <div class="callout info">
        <strong>Research note:</strong> The free plan has important limitations beyond the 50-credit monthly cap: agents are deleted after 14 days of inactivity, and only basic models (not premium ones like GPT-5.2 or Claude Opus) are available. It is useful for testing but not for any real business use.
      </div>
