    <section id="design">
      <h2>Platform &amp; Build Quality</h2>
      <p>Chatbase is a browser-based SaaS platform accessible through any modern web browser. The entire workflow — from training an agent to deploying it across channels — happens through a single dashboard interface. No installation, coding, or developer skills are required.</p>

      <h3>Technology Architecture</h3>
      <p>Chatbase uses Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG). When a visitor asks a question, the platform retrieves the most relevant information from the indexed business data and feeds it to the selected large language model to generate a response. This architecture means the AI answers based on your specific content rather than general knowledge, reducing hallucinations compared to generic chatbots. The data is never used to train AI models — a critical privacy distinction. The platform supports automatic daily retraining, meaning the agent stays current as website content or documents change.</p>

      <h3>AI Model Architecture</h3>
      <p>The defining architectural decision is multi-model support. Most chatbot builders (Tidio, Intercom, Botpress) lock you into a single AI provider or model. Chatbase offers 15+ models from 6 providers: OpenAI (GPT-5.2, GPT-5 Mini, GPT-4o, GPT-4o Mini, GPT-4.5, O3 Mini), Anthropic (Claude Opus 4.6, Claude Opus 4.5, Claude Sonnet 4.5, Claude 3.7 Sonnet, Claude 3.5 Sonnet), Google (Gemini 3 Pro, Gemini 2.5 Pro, Gemini 2.0 Flash), xAI (Grok 4, Grok 3), Moonshot AI (Kimi K2), DeepSeek (V3, R1), and Cohere (Command R+, Command R). You can select a different model per agent and switch at any time. The Playground even lets you compare models side-by-side to evaluate response quality before committing.</p>

      <h3>Security &amp; Compliance</h3>
      <p>Chatbase holds SOC 2 Type II certification with independently audited security controls, is GDPR compliant, uses AES-256 encryption for all data at rest and in transit, and added SSO (Single Sign-On) in January 2026. Additional protections include domain allowlisting, rate limiting, and role-based access controls. The platform runs on AWS infrastructure with data stored in the United States. Crucially, the RAG architecture means customer data is never used to train or fine-tune AI models — it is only retrieved at query time to inform responses.</p>

      <h3>Visual Appeal &amp; Trust Signals</h3>
      <p>The Chatbase website presents a modern, clean interface with clear information hierarchy. Trust signals on the public site include a customer count of 10,000+ businesses, logo walls featuring Chuck E. Cheese, Bridgestone, IHG, National Grid, Opal, Miele, F45 Training, and Noon, an OpenAI testimonial from Marc Manara (Head of Startups), and a SOC 2 certification badge. The platform's rapid development cadence — weekly feature releases throughout early 2026 including SSO, voice input, agent duplication, and 40+ language UI localization — signals an actively maintained product.</p>
