      <h3>Key Features</h3>

      <h4>Custom Knowledge Base Training</h4>
      <p>The core feature. Train your AI agent on 6 types of data: website URLs (automatic crawling), files (PDF, DOCX, TXT, CSV), text, Q&A pairs, Notion pages, and Zendesk/Salesforce support tickets. The agent uses RAG to retrieve relevant information from this data at query time. Automatic daily retraining (configurable) keeps the agent current as content changes. Training content size limits range from 400 KB on Free to 40 MB on Pro.</p>

      <h4>15+ AI Models from 6 Providers</h4>
      <p>Unmatched model selection among chatbot builders. Choose from OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, xAI, DeepSeek, Moonshot AI, and Cohere models — per agent, with side-by-side comparison in the Playground. Model choice directly impacts credit consumption (1-5 credits per response), so users can balance quality against budget. The free plan only offers basic models; all premium models are available from Hobby and above.</p>

      <h4>AI Actions (Task Automation)</h4>
      <p>Beyond Q&A, AI Actions let the agent perform real tasks during conversations: check order status, book meetings (Calendly/Cal.com), process billing queries (Stripe), create support tickets (Zendesk), capture lead information, trigger custom webhooks, and connect to 5,000+ apps via Zapier and Make. Available AI Actions per agent scale from 5 (Hobby) to 12 (Pro). With GPT-5.2, tool-calling accuracy reportedly reaches 98.7%.</p>

      <h4>Multi-Channel Deployment</h4>
      <p>Deploy one AI agent across 6 native channels: website chat widget (embed code or iframe), WhatsApp Business, Facebook Messenger, Instagram DMs, Slack, and Email. Additional channels via Zapier, Make, REST API, and webhooks. The website widget is fully customizable (colors, logo, welcome message, suggested questions). Standalone help page creates a ChatGPT-style interface at a custom domain path.</p>

      <h4>Lead Capture &amp; CRM Integration</h4>
      <p>Configure the agent to collect visitor information (name, email, phone) during conversations. Leads are displayed in a dedicated dashboard with date range filters and CSV export. Integrate with CRMs via Zapier for automated follow-up workflows. This lead capture functionality is one of Chatbase's key differentiators for marketing and sales teams.</p>

      <h4>Smart Escalation</h4>
      <p>Configure natural-language conditions for human handoff — tell the agent in plain language when to escalate (e.g., "if the customer is frustrated" or "if you cannot find the answer"). Escalated conversations route to Zendesk Sunshine, email, or helpdesk tools via integrations. Chatbase does not have built-in live chat for human takeover.</p>

      <h4>Voice AI Agents</h4>
      <p>A newer feature (early 2026) that extends Chatbase beyond text to phone-based AI support. The voice agent handles basic inquiries, provides 24/7 voice availability, and responds in natural-sounding speech. Standard plan and above includes voice and telephony capabilities.</p>

      <h4>Chat Logs, Suggestions &amp; Analytics</h4>
      <p>The Activity tab shows all conversations with confidence scores per response. The "Improve Answer" feature lets you manually correct responses, teaching the agent over time. The Suggestions feature spots knowledge base gaps — if the agent struggles to answer certain questions, Suggestions flags the missing data. Basic analytics are available on Hobby; advanced analytics (topic clustering, satisfaction ratings, missed question detection) are Pro-level features.</p>

      <h3>Areas Requiring Hands-On Validation</h3>
      <p>Several important performance characteristics cannot be assessed from documentation alone. These include: AI response accuracy across different models in real-world scenarios, the actual credit consumption experience and whether the variable pricing creates budget surprises, AI Actions reliability in production (whether the agent correctly executes tasks without errors), widget performance and loading impact on live websites, the quality and usefulness of the analytics and Suggestions features, the real-world experience of the "Improve Answer" workflow, and the point at which a team outgrows Chatbase and needs a full support suite like Intercom or Zendesk. These are noted as open questions from the research.</p>
    </section>

